parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration
inability to control the vehicle's speed
acceleration despite standing on the brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speedometer can lead to inaccurate speed readings, making it difficult for drivers to maintain a safe speed, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Inoperative speedometer
inaccurate speed readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in a loss of vehicle control or accidents.
symptoms: Overheating engine
unusual noises
melted radiator hose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls without warning
stalling on the freeway
vehicle starts immediately after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition assembly interlock can lead to the key being removed from the ignition without placing the transmission in park, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Key can be removed from the ignition without placing the transmission in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause the vehicle to stall or become inoperable, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Battery failure
vehicle unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS control unit can cause the airbags to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The SRS light appears on the dashboard
the airbags fail to deploy in an accident
the SRS control unit requires replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in an accident can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy in an accident
the SRS light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle is involved in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front passenger seat belt anchor slides in and clicks as though it were secure
but comes out of the anchor when pressure is applied
the seat belt does not work properly.

symptoms: The sunroof/moonroof glass shatters or breaks
the sunroof/moonroof flies off while driving
the sunroof/moonroof motor fails.
